  "text": "There are several approaches that exploit the benefits of model-driven architectures for B2B processes [CITATION_1] . A method for modeling cross-organizational processes based on the MDA was proposed [CITATION_2] , which supports the mapping of ARIS models of crossorganizational value chains into BPDM models of abstract (interface) processes. These processes are defined in UML2 activity diagrams. However, the proposed architecture uses a centralized broker to implement and govern B2B interactions. It is different from our approach that encourages the decentralized management of collaborative processes.",
